            "answer_text": "I don\u2019t know of any, except that social science is the investigative tool that researches social behavior and dynamics, and tries to reach conclusions about their governing factors or results. For example, how \u201crole typification\u201d works to define the many roles each person fits into without much formal awareness. Applied social science, then, might be the application of those studies and conclusions to actual cases. For example, when a peer fills the role of a \u201cteacher\u201d to another peer. ",
